"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750935","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-20","<p>Media are frequently invited to public engagements attended by ministers. The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-07-20T16:51:13.41Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750935/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750935/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750935/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-11","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Mass Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many public engagements for which a media calling notice was issued were attended by a departmental Minister in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750936","Department for Education","false","2017-07-24","<p>I am sorry, but information on ministerial attendance at public engagements for which a media calling notice was issued is not readily available or held centrally and could be compiled only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-07-24T15:24:32.687Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750936/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750936/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-11","Department for Education: Mass Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many public engagements for which a media calling notice was issued were attended by a departmental Minister in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750937","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) is the UK customs authority and is responsible for the systems which control goods moving across our borders. Border activity for customs purposes is carried out by Border Force. The resources required by HMRC after the UK leaves the European Union will be dependent on the outcome of negotiations.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:13:26.94Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750937/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750937/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750937/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-11","Customs Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many customs officers are currently employed by HM Revenue and Customs to carry out border activity in the UK; and how many such officers he estimates will be required for such activity after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750938","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>Information on Central Government spend for 2013-14 and 2014-15 can be found online:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/central-government-spend-with-smes-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/central-government-spend-with-smes-2014-to-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>This shows that in 2014-15, Central Government spent over £12 billion (27.1%) with small and medium sized businesses, indicating a continued year on year increase in SMEs winning public procurements.</p><p> </p><p>Data for 2015-16 and 2016-17 will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-07-18T14:37:04.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750938/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750938/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750938/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-11","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of central Government purchasing has come from small and medium-sized enterprises in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750939","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The government has committed to extending a zero rate of VAT to women’s sanitary products as soon as we are legally able to.</p><p> </p><p>Future decisions on VAT will be taken as part of the normal Budget process.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:11:06.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750939/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750939/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750939/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-11","VAT: Tax Rates and Bands","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans to reduce rates of VAT charged on particular goods or services after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4321"
