"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750030","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>Our pay policy has always been designed to strike the right balance between being fair to our public servants and being fair to all those whose taxes pay for them. That approach has not changed and we continually assess that balance.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-07-18T13:11:19.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750030/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750030/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750030/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-10","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans the Government has to remove the public sector pay cap during the course of the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","3921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750031","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-14","<p>The Treasury does not hold information on the organisations or individuals who hold gilts. However, information on gilt holdings by different sectors is published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS). The most recent publication shows that at the end of March 2017, overseas investors hold 27% of gilts in issuance, but this does not include a breakdown of gilt holdings by country.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","3932","2017-07-14T12:17:37.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750031/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750031/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750031/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-10","Government Securities","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will list by country where stocks of gilts are held by overseas investors and foreign central banks; and how much and what proportion of such stocks are held in different countries.","false","Biography information for Neil O'Brien","Harborough","Neil O'Brien","3931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750032","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>I refer the Honourable Lady to my answer of 4 July 2017. It has been the practice of successive administrations not to disclose details of such meetings.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-07-18T13:16:58.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750032/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750032/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750032/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-10","Public Expenditure: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 4 July 2017 to Question 1597, whether the Secretary of State for Scotland has made representations during those discussions for Scotland to receive additional funding as a result of the confidence and supply agreement between the Government and the Democratic Unionist Party.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","3924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750033","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-14","<p>The Treasury does not hold information on the organisations or individuals who hold gilts. However, information on gilt holdings by different sectors is published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS). The most recent publication shows that at the end of March 2017, overseas investors hold 27% of gilts in issuance, but this does not include a breakdown of gilt holdings by country.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","3931","2017-07-14T12:17:37.753Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750033/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750033/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750033/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-10","Public Sector Debt","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will list by country flows of interest payments on UK central Government debt held by overseas investors and foreign central banks.","false","Biography information for Neil O'Brien","Harborough","Neil O'Brien","3932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750034","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Government monitors the impact of tax changes through communication with affected taxpayer groups.</p><p> </p><p>The Government conducted an impact assessment of the reforms to the off-payroll working rules for the whole of the public sector. Further information on the impact assessment can be found in the Tax Information and Impact Note (TIIN), available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/off-payroll-working-in-the-public-sector-changes-to-the-intermediaries-legislation/off-payroll-working-in-the-public-sector-changes-to-the-intermediaries-legislation.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:07:07.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750034/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750034/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750034/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-10","Taxation: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on the NHS of changes to the IR35 regulations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","3933"
