"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750126","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-18","<p>We will provide stability to UK farmers as we leave the EU and the Government has committed to provide the same cash total in funds for farm support until the end of the parliament.</p><p> </p><p>It will be for the Scottish Government to decide on the allocation of funding to individual schemes including the Less Favoured Area Support Scheme for 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The Agriculture Bill will ensure that after we leave the EU we have an effective system in place to support UK farmers and protect our natural environment for future generations. The Secretary of State has spoken to Ministers from Scotland and Wales and officials remain in regular contact with the Northern Ireland Executive. We will continue to engage with the devolved administrations and more widely on the design and the appropriate extent of any legislation.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","3965 ; 3966","2017-07-18T10:52:30.27Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750126/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750126/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750126/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Agriculture: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether it is the Government's policy to (a) maintain or (b) increase the proportion of UK agricultural funding allocated to Scotland under the system that replaces the EU Common Agricultural Policy.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","3964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750127","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-18","<p>We will provide stability to UK farmers as we leave the EU and the Government has committed to provide the same cash total in funds for farm support until the end of the parliament.</p><p> </p><p>It will be for the Scottish Government to decide on the allocation of funding to individual schemes including the Less Favoured Area Support Scheme for 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The Agriculture Bill will ensure that after we leave the EU we have an effective system in place to support UK farmers and protect our natural environment for future generations. The Secretary of State has spoken to Ministers from Scotland and Wales and officials remain in regular contact with the Northern Ireland Executive. We will continue to engage with the devolved administrations and more widely on the design and the appropriate extent of any legislation.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","3964 ; 3965","2017-07-18T10:52:30.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750127/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750127/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750127/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Agriculture: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will make it his policy that farmers and crofters in Scotland will receive at least the same level of support after the UK leaves the EU as they do at present.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","3966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750128","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-18","<p>We will provide stability to UK farmers as we leave the EU and the Government has committed to provide the same cash total in funds for farm support until the end of the parliament.</p><p> </p><p>It will be for the Scottish Government to decide on the allocation of funding to individual schemes including the Less Favoured Area Support Scheme for 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The Agriculture Bill will ensure that after we leave the EU we have an effective system in place to support UK farmers and protect our natural environment for future generations. The Secretary of State has spoken to Ministers from Scotland and Wales and officials remain in regular contact with the Northern Ireland Executive. We will continue to engage with the devolved administrations and more widely on the design and the appropriate extent of any legislation.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","3964 ; 3966","2017-07-18T10:52:30.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750128/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750128/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750128/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will make it his policy to guarantee funding for the Less Favoured Area Support Scheme for 2019.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","3965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750129","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-18","<p>Neither Defra nor the Forestry Commission records the planting data of projects that are not funded directly by either Defra or FC. Many local authorities fund their own tree planting projects; therefore, they record their own planting data. As the information requested is not collated centrally it could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics on the total new planting in England (in hectares), including planting from all other recorded sources, are available from the Forestry Commission’s Woodland Area, Planting and Publicly Funded Restocking publication: <a href="https://www.forestry.gov.uk/forestry/infd-7aqknx" target="_blank">https://www.forestry.gov.uk/forestry/infd-7aqknx</a></p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","4118","2017-07-18T16:43:04.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750129/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750129/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750129/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Tree Planting: Public Places","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many trees have been planted in public spaces in the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","4117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750130","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-18","<p>Neither Defra nor the Forestry Commission records the planting data of projects that are not funded directly by either Defra or FC. Many local authorities fund their own tree planting projects; therefore, they record their own planting data. As the information requested is not collated centrally it could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics on the total new planting in England (in hectares), including planting from all other recorded sources, are available from the Forestry Commission’s Woodland Area, Planting and Publicly Funded Restocking publication: <a href="https://www.forestry.gov.uk/forestry/infd-7aqknx" target="_blank">https://www.forestry.gov.uk/forestry/infd-7aqknx</a></p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","4117","2017-07-18T16:43:04.46Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750130/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750130/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750130/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Tree Planting: Southampton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many trees have been planted in Southampton in the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","4118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750131","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-17","<ol><li><p>80 consignments of dogs were exported from Great Britain to the EU during 2016 with individual health certificates, under the Balai Directive. This figure does not include those which moved under the pet travel scheme.</p><p> </p></li><li><p>3886 consignments of dogs were exported from Great Britain to non-EU countries during 2016.</p><p> </p></li></ol>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-07-17T11:36:51.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750131/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750131/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750131/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Dogs: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many consignments of dogs were exported from the UK to (a) EU and (b) non-EU countries in 2016.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","3804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750132","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Government has a clear goal that nearly all cars and vans should be zero emission by 2050, and we want people across the UK to benefit from electric vehicles as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for Low Emission Vehicles provides a range of grant support to make electric vehicle ownership more affordable. The plug-in car grant offers up to £4,500 off the cost of an eligible electric car, and there is similar financial support for other vehicles, including motorcycles, vans, taxis and buses. Vehicles are increasingly becoming available on the second-hand car market, which makes electric vehicles a viable option for many more people. For both new and second-hand electric vehicle owners there is grant support to help with the cost of a home chargepoint – including for those without off-street parking.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>This support is offered regardless of household income and the data is not collected to undertake the analysis requested.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-07-18T16:45:18.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750132/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750132/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750132/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to meet its air quality targets by supporting people from low-income backgrounds to buy (a) hybrid and (b) electric vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","Mr William Wragg","3770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750133","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-20","<p>Across the UK, 259 local authorities have declared Air Quality Management Areas (AQMAs). The breakdown by pollutants and region is provided on the UK-AIR website: <a href="https://uk-air.defra.gov.uk/aqma/list" target="_blank">https://uk-air.defra.gov.uk/aqma/list</a>.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-07-20T17:12:57.237Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750133/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750133/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750133/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-10","Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many local authorities have declared an air quality management area.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","3733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750134","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>The creation of new central registers or similarly effective systems has been completed in all the Crown Dependencies (CDs) and in the following Overseas Territories with financial centres: Bermuda, The British Virgin Islands, The Cayman Islands &amp; Gibraltar, with legislation to underpin the registers passed by their respective legislatures. Data population of the registers with data will be taken forward as a priority in coming months.</p><p>Guernsey and Alderney's legislation to enable their registers to be operational will be considered by the Privy Council this month.</p><p>The Turks and Caicos Islands have passed legislation, and their register is expected to be operational by the end of this month.</p><p>Anguilla has not yet established its register. We continue to engage with the Anguillian authorities to take this forward.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-18T12:14:28.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750134/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750134/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750134/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","Companies: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether all Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies have central registers of beneficial ownership in operation; and what plans he has to make those registers public.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Dame Margaret Hodge","3734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750135","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-20","<p>The laws of the British Indian Ocean Territory do not provide for a legal minimum wage.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-20T07:40:44.5Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750135/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750135/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750135/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","British Indian Ocean Territory: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the legal minimum wage is in the British Indian Ocean Territory.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","3766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750136","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-20","<p>Since 1 January 2015, the Government Legal Department has raised invoices in the sum of £128,113 in respect of litigation brought by Chagossian interest groups in relation to the British Indian Ocean Territory.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-20T07:50:30.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750136/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750136/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750136/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","British Indian Ocean Territory: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to his Department's freedom of information case FOI2007-15 on legal costs and Chagos Islands, what additional cost to the public purse has been incurred in the Bancoult, Chagos Refugee Group and Chagos Islanders case since 4 February 2015.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","3792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750137","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>Allies, in a strict legal sense, are those states with whom the UK has a Treaty-based commitment to militarily assist each other in the event of an armed attack. As such I can confirm that all of the UK’s allies are governed by forms of parliamentary or other representative democracy.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-07-18T12:32:39.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750137/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750137/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750137/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","Democracy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which countries that are allies of the UK are not governed through some form of parliamentary democracy.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","3844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750138","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-13","<p>As we have throughout this case, we continue to raise the case with the Indian authorities at all levels. The case was most recently raised by the Prime Minister with Indian Prime Minister Modi at the G20 in Hamburg last week.</p><p>We understand the impact the separation of six families is having and how the wait for a verdict is increasing the stress and financial strain on them. We make that point when we raise the case with the Indian authorities. However, we cannot interfere in what is an ongoing legal process, just as we would not allow another country to interfere in an ongoing court case in the United Kingdom.</p><p>While we await a verdict our High Commission in India remains in close contact with the men's legal team in India and in the UK, and our focus continues to be on the men's welfare and the support we can provide to their families.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-07-13T13:05:02.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750138/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750138/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750138/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","India: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Government of India on behalf of the six ex-Army personnel being held in Chennai Jail.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","3900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750139","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>The annual running costs for 1 Carlton Gardens are shown below:</p><p>Financial year 2010/11 £751,802</p><p>Financial year 2011/12 £766,524</p><p>Financial year 2012/13 £721,231</p><p>Financial year 2013/14 £740,332</p><p>Financial year 2014/15 £933,736</p><p>Financial year 2015/16 £850,099</p><p>Financial year 2016/17 £984,491</p><p>The rise between 2013/14 and 2014/15 was due to an increase in annual rent (following a Crown Estates rent review). The rise between 2015/2016 and 2016/17 was primarily due to increased security costs.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-07-18T15:42:29.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750139/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750139/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750139/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","1 Carlton Gardens: Operating Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the annual running costs of No. 1 Carlton Gardens were in each of the last seven years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","3849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750140","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>​We have received no formal representations on this issue. Nationally we follow the political situation in West Papua closely and raise human rights concerns, wherever we have them, with the Indonesians.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-07-18T12:36:30.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750140/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750140/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750140/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","Papua: Crimes against Humanity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has received on the alleged genocide in West Papua.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750141","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Foreign Secretary last met the Iraqi Minister of Foreign Affairs, Dr. Ibrahim Al-Jaafari, on 3 July in London.</p><p>Their discussions covered; the UK's strong and continuing support for Iraq as it defeats Daesh; the importance of an inclusive political settlement in Mosul and other liberated areas; rebuilding a sense of national identity; the upcoming elections in Iraq; the Kurdish Regional Government's intention to hold a referendum on independence; and progress on the Campaign to Bring Daesh to Justice.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-07-18T15:33:37.69Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750141/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750141/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750141/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","Iraq: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last met his Iraqi counterpart; and what issues were discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750142","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-13","<p>​The British Government regularly raises the issue of women’s rights, including the strict anti-abortion laws with the Government of El Salvador. The then FCO Minister of State (Baroness Anelay) raised these issues when she visited El Salvador in December 2016 and the Minister of State for Europe and the Americas (Sir Alan Duncan) has raised our concerns with the Salvadoran Ambassador in London both in person and in writing.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-07-13T13:00:01.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750142/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750142/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750142/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","El Salvador: Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterpart in El Salvador on potential reform of abortion laws in that country.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","4027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750143","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-13","<p>Our Embassy in Bahrain is seeking further information from the authorities concerning the details of these cases. The UK continues to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments. We also encourage those with concerns about treatment in detention to report these to the Ministry of Interior Ombudsman.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-07-13T15:37:41.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750143/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750143/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-10","Bahrain: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterparts in the Bahrain Government on the treatment of (a) Ebtisam Al-Sayegh and (b) Mohammed Khalil al Shakouri.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","4041"
