"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750297","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-17","<p>Neither the Department nor local authorities have powers to charge operators for using portable traffic signals. In any event, the decision as to whether to use portable traffic signals or some other form of traffic management at a particular street or road works site should be determined by reference to the guidance in our statutory code of practice <em>Safety at Street Works and Road Works</em> and a site-specific risk assessment. It would not be appropriate to charge operators for using portable traffic signals if they considered them to be necessary for safety.</p><p> </p><p>To comply with the statutory code of practice <em>Safety at Street Works and Road Works</em>, operators that propose using portable traffic signals also have to obtain permission from the relevant highway authority before they are installed. The highway authority can reject such proposals if they do not consider them to be appropriate. We believe that sufficient controls are in place, and therefore have no plans to regulate the use of portable traffic signals further.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","4077","2017-07-17T16:05:47.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750297/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750297/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Traffic Lights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what powers (a) his Department and (b) local authorities have to charge operators for its installation of mobile traffic lights.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","4078"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750298","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-18","<p>I refer the Honourable Member for Stretford and Urmston to the answer given by my Right Hon Friend, the Minister for the Cabinet Office, the Right Honourable Member for Ashford in response to UIN 3079 on 11 July.</p><p> </p><p>The Race Disparity Audit will publish Government data about ethnicity on a website. The data will show the ethnic classifications available for each dataset covered, including where available Gypsies and Travellers.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","3876","2017-07-18T08:31:18.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750298/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750298/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Department for Transport: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the oral Answer of 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, what steps his Department has taken to use 2011 census classifications, including on Gypsies and Travellers, to audit racial disparities in public service outcomes.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","4062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750299","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-17","<p>Neither the Department nor local authorities have powers to charge operators for using portable traffic signals. In any event, the decision as to whether to use portable traffic signals or some other form of traffic management at a particular street or road works site should be determined by reference to the guidance in our statutory code of practice <em>Safety at Street Works and Road Works</em> and a site-specific risk assessment. It would not be appropriate to charge operators for using portable traffic signals if they considered them to be necessary for safety.</p><p> </p><p>To comply with the statutory code of practice <em>Safety at Street Works and Road Works</em>, operators that propose using portable traffic signals also have to obtain permission from the relevant highway authority before they are installed. The highway authority can reject such proposals if they do not consider them to be appropriate. We believe that sufficient controls are in place, and therefore have no plans to regulate the use of portable traffic signals further.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","4078","2017-07-17T16:05:47.72Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750299/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750299/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Traffic Lights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will regulate the use of mobile traffic lights to ensure sufficient warning is given to road users.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","4077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750300","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-18","<p>Compensation for passengers is set out in the Passenger’s Charter of the franchised train operator in question. Heathrow Express has its own arrangements for compensation.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-18T12:57:46.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750300/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750300/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Paddington Station: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what compensation arrangements are in place to support passengers affected by the recent closures at Paddington station.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","4076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750301","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-18","<p>Officials and ministers meet train operators and Network Rail regularly to discuss rail performance. Resilience of the rail network infrastructure is a matter for Network Rail.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-18T08:03:48.5Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750301/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750301/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Paddington Station: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he plans to take to assess the resilience of Great Western Railway as a result of the recent closures of Paddington station.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","4075"
