"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750303","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-18","<p>I refer the Honourable Member for Stretford and Urmston to the answer given by my Right Hon Friend, the Minister for the Cabinet Office, the Right Honourable Member for Ashford in response to UIN 3079 on 11 July.</p><p> </p><p>The Race Disparity Audit will publish Government data about ethnicity on a website. The data will show the ethnic classifications available for each dataset covered, including where available Gypsies and Travellers.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","4062","2017-07-18T08:31:18.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750303/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750303/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750303/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Department for Transport: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the contribution from the Minister for the Cabinet Office on 2 November 2016, Official Report, column 879, what work is being done to progress work to distinguish Gypsies and Travellers using 2011 census classifications in his Department.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750304","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>We plan to publish the Government’s response later this year. We recognise the need to provide the UK biofuel industry with certainty if it is to realise the industrial opportunities highlighted in the consultation. It is therefore our intention to implement changes to the Renewable Transport Fuel Obligation as soon as possible.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-13T15:44:01.92Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750304/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750304/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750304/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Renewable Transport Fuel Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the Government plans to publish its response to the consultation on the proposed changes to the Renewable Transport Fuel Obligation Order.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","3892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750305","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>This is a matter for the Scottish Government, who have executive devolved responsibilities in relation to the railway infrastructure in Scotland.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T11:44:08.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750305/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750305/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Railways: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with Network Rail on the Edinburgh to Glasgow Improvement Programme works.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","4050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750306","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>There have been no discussions between the Secretary of State for Transport and the Chancellor of the Exchequer on Rail Fares policy since the 13 June 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Officials from the Department of Transport and HM Treasury officials have regular working level coordination meetings covering a range of issues including rail fares policy.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T15:50:58.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750306/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750306/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Railways: Fares","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions (a) he and (b) officials of his Department have had with (i) the Chancellor of  the Exchequer and (ii) officials of HM Treasury on rail fares policy since 13 June 2017.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750308","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Department frequently holds discussions with Network Rail about the environmental impact of the railway, including measures to mitigate noise and vibration.</p><p> </p><p>More widely, the UK has also been involved in discussions with the European Commission and other EU Member States about proposed changes to the Technical Specifications for Interoperability that deals with Noise and how this might apply to freight wagons. These discussions are still ongoing.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T11:10:38.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750308/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750308/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Railways: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with Network Rail on noise and vibration pollution caused by certain types of freight wagons in use on the rail network; and whether any changes to regulations (a) have been or (b) are under consideration to reduce noise and vibration pollution.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","3753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750309","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Office of Rail and Road is responsible for monitoring Network Rail’s performance and whether the company is complying with the obligations set out in its licence. This includes a twice-yearly publication through its Network Rail Monitor document.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-13T11:46:57.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750309/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750309/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Railways: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment the Government has made of the effectiveness of Network Rail's re-planning of Control Period 5.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","3812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750310","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Department for Transport (DfT) has postponed publication of its annual 2016 road casualty data until 28 September as a result of a delay in receiving final validated data from Transport for London (TfL), in particular the data which TfL receives and processes for the Metropolitan Police Service (MPS). The MPS data makes up around 15% of the road casualty dataset for Great Britain and therefore a significant component of the national total. The Department for Transport is working closely with TfL to obtain final validated data from the MPS.</p><p> </p><p>The procedures for submitting reported road casualty data to DfT are well established and outlined in the published manuals detailing the instructions for completion of accident records and how these records should be checked for accuracy. It is the responsibility of those organisations supplying the data to DfT, either directly from police forces or via highway authorities, to ensure that accident records meet the required quality standards. DfT has regular contact with all data suppliers and works with them to identify any errors in the data on a continuous basis.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-18T08:09:15.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750310/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750310/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that road accident and casualty statistics are published on time; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","3841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750311","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-18","<p>The British Road Safety statement sets out the Department for Transport’s vision, values and priorities in relation to British road safety. Local Authorities and the police are free to set casualty reduction targets, if they find it useful.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-18T08:21:08.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750311/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750311/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the Government's policy is on reducing deaths and injuries to road users; and if he will adopt casualty reduction targets.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","3843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750312","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>No cost-benefit analysis has been carried out by the Department for these proposals. Decisions about which local transport schemes to fund are the responsibility of the relevant local authority.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","3791","2017-07-13T12:01:47.74Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750312/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750312/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Cycling: Oxfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has conducted a cost-benefit analysis on proposals to build a community cycle path along the B4044 from Eynsham to Botley.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","3790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750313","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-13","<p>No cost-benefit analysis has been carried out by the Department for these proposals. Decisions about which local transport schemes to fund are the responsibility of the relevant local authority.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","3790","2017-07-13T12:01:47.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750313/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750313/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-10","Cycling: Oxfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has conducted a cost-benefit analysis on proposals to build a cycle route from Oxford to Didcot.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","3791"
