"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750319","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>At June 2017, the average duration of telephone calls to the Universal Credit Digital (Full Service) telephone line was 5 minutes and 53 seconds.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes</strong>: Please note that the data supplied is derived from unpublished management information which was collected for internal Departmental use only and has not been quality assured to National Statistics or Official Statistics publication standard. The data should therefore be treated with caution.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Source: BT</strong> - Operational Management Information System (OPMIS)</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-18T16:25:28.543Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750319/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750319/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750319/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Universal Credit: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of the average length of telephone calls it receives from universal credit claimants in areas where the universal credit full digital service is being rolled out.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","3864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750320","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The gathering of medical evidence is a key part of the claim process and the information is gathered from a range of sources. However, the information as requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-13T12:31:28.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750320/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750320/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750320/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Social Security Benefits: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, in what proportion of disability benefit claims his Department asks a claimant's doctor for medical evidence directly rather than seeking that evidence through the claimant.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","3887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750321","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-17","<p>The date of the last Ministerial visit to the Torrington Jobcentre Plus could only be provided at disproportionate costs.</p><p> </p><p>However, it can be confirmed that since May 2015, there have been no visits to the above Jobcentre Plus by the Secretary of State or his Ministers.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-17T10:59:17.983Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750321/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750321/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Jobcentres: Coventry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, on which date (a) he or (b) a Minister of his Department last visited Torrington Avenue Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750322","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-17","<p>The date of the last Ministerial visit to the Cofa Court Jobcentre Plus could only be provided at disproportionate costs.</p><p> </p><p>However, it can be confirmed that since May 2015, there have been no visits to the above Jobcentre Plus by the Secretary of State or his Ministers.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-17T10:59:42.42Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750322/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750322/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Jobcentres: Coventry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, on which date (a) he or (b) a Minister of his Department last visited Cofa Court Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750323","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>BPDTS Ltd was set-up to provide IT services to DWP previously provided by Hewlett Packard Enterprises Ltd. The Secretary of State is the sole member of the company and therefore in effect its owner.</p><p> </p><p>There are two Executive Directors (the Chief Executive and the Chief Financial Officer) both of whom are civil servants, employed by DWP. The Chief Executive spends approximately 75% of his time on BPDTS business and the Chief Financial Officer 100% of his time.</p><p> </p><p>There are five non-Executive Directors who are also senior officers of DWP. The time they spent on the company’s business is limited to attendance at monthly Board meetings and preparations for those meetings.</p><p> </p><p>Service orders identifying work to be undertaken by BPDTS Ltd are agreed with the DWP Digital Group.</p><p> </p><p>There is no financial benefit in awarding this work to any Director.</p><p> </p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-07-13T13:16:09.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750323/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750323/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750323/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","BPDTS","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of the time of directors of the Benefits and Pensions Digital Technology Services Limited (BPDTS) is spent as (a) employees of his Department and (b) employees of BPDTS; who in his Department awards work to BPDTS; whether there is any financial benefit to those directors from work awarded by his Department to that company; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","3829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750324","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>We believe that it is a reasonable expectation that claimants travel to an office within three miles or 20 minutes by public transport of their existing jobcentre. This may mean slightly longer and slightly shorter journeys for some individual claimants who use our services in the North West and we have considered this when setting the criteria. There are large areas of the country where claimants have always travelled further than this without any issues.</p><p> </p><p>We have assessed the distances between existing and new jobcentre locations to help customers better understand any differences in time and distance. This is to reflect the fact that people who travel to the jobcentre will use whichever type of transport suits their personal circumstances, they may not be starting their journey from their home, and not all those who use our services are claimants.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-13T09:25:18.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750324/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750324/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Jobcentres: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the proposed closure of a number of jobcentres in the North West on travelling time and distance for claimants.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","4046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750325","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>The planned changes at Linacre House, Bootle will help us to deliver better services in the future as well as reduce the amount we spend on leasing buildings. We have looked at how we can rationalise the work, whilst ensuring that we do not diminish our service or lose any knowledge and experience.</p><p> </p><p>We will transfer the work and processing colleagues to St Martins House, Bootle. The services undertaken at Linacre House are not specifically linked to claims made by people in the surrounding area and is part of a national network of processing sites. We do not anticipate any impact on the service to claimants in the local area as a result of these changes.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-13T09:16:07.617Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750325/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750325/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Department for Work and Pensions: Bootle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the closure of his Department's processing and contact centre in Bootle Linacre on the response times for caseload in the local area.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","4049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750326","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-17","<p>Between April 2013 and April 2017 there have been 6,430 initial decisions on claims for Personal Independence Payment in the Vale of Clwyd. In this same period, 340 had their Award Changed at mandatory reconsideration.</p><p> </p><p>Tribunal Statistics, including appeal outcomes are published by the Ministry of Justice and so we will not be able to provide consistent regional breakdown of these statistics for the Vale of Clwyd. We would recommend requesting this information from the Ministry of Justice.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-17T11:00:54.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750326/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750326/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Personal Independence Payment: Vale of Clwyd","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of constituents in the Vale of Clwyd constituency have had their original personal independence payments overturned as a result of (a) mandatory reconsideration or (b) an appeal hearing in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","3981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750327","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>The application of the Local Housing Allowance rate to supported housing will be deferred until 2019/20. Developing a workable and sustainable funding model for supported housing is a priority for the Government. We will set out further details on our plans as soon as possible.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-13T09:28:34.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750327/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750327/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Housing Benefit: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether people with mental or physical health problems living in supported housing will be exempt from the local housing allowance rate cap for housing benefit.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","3888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750328","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>The optimum caseload of a work coach in Live Service is dependent on a number of factors, including the level of customer support required and the demographics of the surrounding area.</p><p> </p><p>In Full Service it is too early to assess what the optimum work coach caseload will be. The service continues to develop iteratively, with claimants able to increasingly self-serve and interact with their work coach on-line.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-13T15:17:36.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750328/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750328/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the optimum number of universal credit claimants for the caseload of a work coach in a (a) live service and (b) full digital service area.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","4030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750329","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Universal Credit Full (Digital) Service continues to roll-out as planned. Since November 2014 when the first jobcentre went live we have continued to test, learn and refine the service as it has expanded. We are seeing steady improvements in processing as the new service beds in and claimants adjust to the new system. The full service is now operating in 93 jobcentres and we plan to continue to improve and develop the service as the roll-out accelerates.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-13T15:13:49.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750329/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750329/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Universal Credit: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the roll-out of the universal credit full digital service to date.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","4029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750330","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Department’s guidance directs staff dealing with Universal Credit claims to call customers back either if they request it or if they express any concern about the cost of calling.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-13T10:15:10.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750330/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750330/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Universal Credit: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Answer of 1 March 2016 to Question 27621, what guidance his Department provides to its staff on proactively making callers who want to discuss universal credit aware that staff can call them back free of charge.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","4028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750331","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>Jobseekers Allowance (JSA) can be claimed when Employment and Support Allowance has stopped, while waiting for a decision on a MR or appeal, subject to JSA normal conditions of entitlement. No separate assessment has been made of the cost effectiveness of JSA for this group.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-18T11:22:38.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750331/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750331/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of (a) the cost-effectiveness and (b) resource efficiency of employment and support allowance claimants who have been found fit to work claiming jobseeker's allowance while waiting for the result of a mandatory reconsideration.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","3774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750332","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>a) To ensure that the outcome of assessments conducted by his Department on people seeking to claim employment and support allowance are correct</p><p> </p><p>With regard to the actual Work Capability Assessment (WCA), the Department robustly monitors the performance of the Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (CHDA). They are independently audited to ensure that the advice provided to the Department’s decision makers is of suitable quality, fully explained, and justified. Assessment reports deemed unacceptable are returned to CHDA for reworking. The Department continues to work extensively with the assessment provider to make improvements to guidance, training and audit procedures in order to ensure that a quality service is maintained. All healthcare professionals delivering assessments for CHDA complete rigorous training before they are allowed to undertake WCAs. The healthcare professionals employed by CHDA are required to complete the agreed elements of Continuing Medical Education, as set out in the contract each year. CHDA undertake continuous review and audit of all healthcare professionals, with clinical mentoring available as required.</p><p> </p><p>b) To reduce the number of decisions based on such assessments which are overturned on appeal.</p><p> </p><p>Any claimant wishing to dispute a decision made based on their assessment is entitled to do so.</p><p> </p><p>The first stage of which is for the Department to conduct a Mandatory Reconsideration (MR) whereby a different decision maker undertakes a full review of the case and considers any additional evidence provided. The Department undertakes this review in an attempt to ensure before appeal that our decision is as robust and accurate as possible.</p><p> </p><p>However, should the decision remain the same and the claimant still disagree, they can submit an appeal directly with Her Majesty’s Court and Tribunal Service (HMCTS).</p><p> </p><p>The Department now has Presenting Officers attending 50% of all ESA Appeals at HMCTS ensuring that where the Department believes the decision to be robust and accurate, we are adequately represented. This also enables us to gather significant feedback that will inform the quality of our decision making going forward.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-18T14:18:19.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750332/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750332/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Employment and Support Allowance: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to (a) ensure that the outcome of assessments conducted by his Department on people seeking to claim employment and support allowance are correct and (b) reduce the number of decisions based on such assessments which are overturned on appeal.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","3772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750333","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>The department operates 382 ‘0345’ telephone numbers.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-18T15:05:44.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750333/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750333/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Department for Work and Pensions: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many 0345 telephone numbers his Department operates.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","3846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750334","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>The range of average speed of answer to the Universal Credit Live Service, Universal Credit Digital (Full Service) and 0345 telephone lines (excluding Universal Credit) are shown in the table below. Mean average waiting times are not recorded.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Range Shortest</p></td><td><p>Range Longest</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Universal Credit - Live Service</p></td><td><p>2 minutes 28 seconds<br> (July 2016)</p></td><td><p>4 minutes 24 seconds<br> (January 2017)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Universal Credit Digital (Full Service)</p></td><td><p>1 minute 38 seconds<br> (April 2017)</p></td><td><p>13 minutes 18 seconds<br> (November 2016)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All other 0345 Lines (excluding Universal Credit)</p></td><td><p>2 minutes 24 seconds<br> (January 2017)</p></td><td><p>4 minutes 3 seconds<br> (September 2016)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes</strong>: Please note that the data supplied is derived from unpublished management information which was collected for internal Departmental use only and has not been quality assured to National Statistics or Official Statistics publication standard. The data should therefore be treated with caution. Performance variation should be viewed in the context of a wide range of operational impacts occurring; this includes caller demand, system stability, changes to process and adviser capacity.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Source: BT</strong> - Operational Management Information System (OPMIS)</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-18T16:32:18.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750334/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750334/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Department for Work and Pensions: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of the (a) longest and (b) mean waiting times to his Department's (i) universal credit helpline and (ii) 0345 phone lines.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","3847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750335","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>From 6 April 2018 a new loans-based system of support for mortgage interest will replace the current benefits based provision. Eligible owner-occupier recipients of income-based Jobseeker’s Allowance, income-related Employment and Support Allowance, Income Support, Pension Credit and Universal Credit will be offered interest-bearing loans that give the same level of protection against repossession as current provision. These loans will be secured against their property and repaid from available equity when the property is sold.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","3742","2017-07-18T14:52:24.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750335/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750335/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Mortgages: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether it is the Government's policy that support for mortgage interest will become an interest-bearing loan secured against the mortgaged property from April 2018.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750336","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>From 6 April 2018 a new loans-based system of support for mortgage interest will replace the current benefits based provision. Eligible owner-occupier recipients of income-based Jobseeker’s Allowance, income-related Employment and Support Allowance, Income Support, Pension Credit and Universal Credit will be offered interest-bearing loans that give the same level of protection against repossession as current provision. These loans will be secured against their property and repaid from available equity when the property is sold.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","3727","2017-07-18T14:52:24.36Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750336/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750336/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750336/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Mortgages: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the Government's policy from April 2018 will be on support for mortgage interest.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750337","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-17","<p>Until November 2018, claimants with more than two children cannot normally make a new claim for Universal Credit and are directed to claim Child Tax Credit. Thereafter, new claims from families with more than two children will be taken through Universal Credit. Families with two or more children already on Universal Credit who have a third or subsequent child from April 2017 will remain on Universal Credit.</p><p /><p />","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-17T14:40:19.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750337/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750337/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the Government's policy is on families with more than two children claiming universal credit and child tax credit.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750338","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>As the Chancellor announced at Budget last year, the existing Employer Supported Childcare scheme will remain open to new entrants until April 2018.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","3728","2017-07-18T13:08:56.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750338/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750338/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-10","Child Care Vouchers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on new claims for employer support childcare vouchers from April 2018.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750339","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-18","<p>Pensions Dashboards are an exciting idea and the Government worked with industry to deliver a working prototype of the dashboard in April 2017. However, the development of dashboards is still at a very early stage with many policy questions outstanding, The single financial guidance body is in the early stages of being passed through Parliament so it is too early to determine the entire role of the body.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-07-18T16:03:31.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750339/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/750339/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-10","Pensions: Consumer Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether the new single financial guidance body will host a pensions dashboard.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","4095"
